Peekaboo | Dalanzadgad, 🇲🇳 Mongolia
///torched.craggy.stockpile

Upon arriving in Dalanzadgad (Даланзадгад), I needed to find a good hotel, so I checked my Lonely Planet guide book and found one that was highly rated. Sadly, the name and addresses in this town were in Cyrillic, so even in the city I needed my trusty 3 word address to find it! I asked them hotel for a room that faced the mountains, and that night a thunderstorm rolled in and I couldn’t see a thing. The next morning, however, the storm was clearing, the sun forcing its way out, and the mountains majestically peeking through the clouds. For some reason I didn’t expect to see this type of landscape in Mongolia, but I was very happy when it appeared! Don't forget to check out my Lonely Planet takeover to see some exclusive photos!
