The Camel Rider | Gobi Desert, 🇲🇳 Mongolia
///segregated.concerto.stallion

If you’d been watching my IG Stories, you would have seen me exploring some of the remote places around Mongolia, for @lonelyplanet and @what3words, two of my very favourite companies. As I’m sure you’re aware, the Lonely Planet guides (online and print) help you discover cool places to visit. Due to Mongolia being so sparse and having no real roads or addresses, what3words allows me to locate these places, because Lonely Planet now has 3 word addresses for most of their Mongolia listings. This makes me so happy! Stay tuned or some more photos from Mongolia this week, plus my Lonely Planet takeover at the weekend.
____
@lonelyplanet @what3words #lonelyplanet #what3words #lpPathfinders

Mongolian Nights | Baasanhuu Family Ger Camp, 🇲🇳 Mongolia
///beanbag.skier.pigments

When I arrived in Mongolia, I was hoping that I’d get a chance to shoot the Milky Way, as there is next to no light pollution. Sadly, most nights had torrential thunderstorms. Thankfully this night, the skies remained clear and the stars came out to play. If you recall the man on the camel in my other photo, his name is Baasanhuu and he owns this ger camp. Without the 3 word address in the guide book, I really would have struggled to find this camp. Why not find “beanbag.skier.pigments” for yourself and see how remote this camp is!
